  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nNeed more time to monitor, but seems like peers don't want to stay long with Lodestar v1.9.0-rc.0 (this is on a test mainnet node)\r\n\r\n<img width=\"800\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-26 at 12 49 11\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/9260b80b-7765-4ca4-8278-8094ded84a03\">\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1287\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-26 at 12 56 20\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/0e5f1608-79ac-4d43-ad0e-9749296986cd\">\r\n\r\nmore bad behavior reported due to dial error and timeouts\r\n\r\n<img width=\"799\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-26 at 12 50 34\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/104f701e-bbfa-42ef-b953-1ca279761df6\">\r\n\r\nmore goodbye received\r\n<img width=\"781\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-26 at 12 50 49\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/22cdf8b1-dabb-4dc4-8f2f-0b6efce5f77c\">\r\n\r\nmore incoming request handler errors and request/response roundtrip time\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1585\" alt=\"Screenshot 2023-05-26 at 12 53 03\" src=\"https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/assets/10568965/c9cf2b42-de12-4291-a1a8-e787b03d7134\">\r\n\r\n\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nstable peers\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- this happens on mainnet node only, don't see it happens to goerli nodes\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating system\n\nLinux\n\n### Lodestar version or commit hash\n\nv1.9.0-rc.0",
